1
00:00:03,600 --> 00:00:05,240
Why are you driving from here?
-Why not?

2
00:00:05,320 --> 00:00:06,400
Because it makes the trip longer.

3
00:00:06,480 --> 00:00:08,800
It's the same thing.
-No. There are a ton of traffic lights from here.

4
00:00:09,400 --> 00:00:12,440
What does it matter? We get there in the end?
-Fine. Look, look, check it out,

5
00:00:12,520 --> 00:00:15,000
On the right. A girl with a bomb is passing you.
-Do you want to drive?

6
00:00:15,080 --> 00:00:16,480
No.
-Then let me drive in peace.

7
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:19,200
It can't be that every time we
go to my parents' place, you freak out.

8
00:00:19,320 --> 00:00:21,680
I'm not freaking out, and it has nothing to do with your parents.
-No, what?

9
00:00:21,760 --> 00:00:24,000
No, it’s not related. It’s your parents, and everything’s fine with them.

10
00:00:24,480 --> 00:00:26,640
I'm just annoyed about the jeans.
-What's wrong with these?

11
00:00:26,760 --> 00:00:30,480
Not these. The ones that didn't fit me at home.
-Oh, it's allowed,

12
00:00:30,560 --> 00:00:34,800
You're as beautiful as the night I met you.
-In the army? When I was 10 kg heavier?

13
00:00:35,200 --> 00:00:39,680
15. But 15 charming ones.
-Idiot.

14
00:00:44,120 --> 00:00:46,720
Look at me, look at me and...

15
00:00:56,080 --> 00:00:57,000
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

16
00:00:57,080 --> 00:00:59,240
Hi. Where have you been?

17
00:00:59,840 --> 00:01:03,320
I was already worried. Hey.
-What's up, Riki?

18
00:01:03,480 --> 00:01:05,560
Don't ask who died, and no one touch the phone.

19
00:01:07,600 --> 00:01:10,920
Who died?
-Uncle Shmuel.

20
00:01:11,080 --> 00:01:12,920
Would you believe it?
-Well, it was expected, right?

21
00:01:13,720 --> 00:01:16,120
He passed away last night.
-Oh, poor thing.

22
00:01:16,200 --> 00:01:18,360
That's how it is, sit down, you never
know when you'll die.

23
00:01:18,920 --> 00:01:23,240
You look a bit pale, you know?
-No.

24
00:01:23,320 --> 00:01:26,840
And the phone?
-From Miami.

25
00:01:27,520 --> 00:01:29,280
Today they’re opening the will and will call to update me,

26
00:01:29,840 --> 00:01:33,200
so no one touch the phone.

27
00:01:33,360 --> 00:01:35,000
Tell the girls too.
-Okay.

28
00:01:35,080 --> 00:01:36,080
Excuse me, I'm going to flip
the schnitzels so they don't burn.

29
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:39,240
Do you need help, Riki?
-No, sweetie.

30
00:01:39,320 --> 00:01:41,040
I'm already used to doing everything alone.

31
00:01:41,240 --> 00:01:43,200
Okay, I just don’t understand. Why does she
need to say things like that to me?

32
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:47,280
She can't help it, it's in her genes.
-Uncle Shmuel, huh?

33
00:01:47,360 --> 00:01:49,480
She waited for this for weeks.
-Weeks is just the time we've known each other.

34
00:01:49,960 --> 00:01:52,800
It started even before.
-What? You think there's a chance for something in the inheritance?

35
00:01:52,880 --> 00:01:57,000
I don’t know. She took care of him really well all those years,

36
00:01:57,600 --> 00:01:59,960
always insisted he stay here when he visited

37
00:02:00,160 --> 00:02:01,680
even though he could rent out the whole
Hilton. She might get something.

38
00:02:02,240 --> 00:02:04,880
Not for her. For the son. Does the son have a chance?
-No, no, I don’t think so.

39
00:02:04,960 --> 00:02:08,560
We never got along.
-Really?

40
00:02:08,639 --> 00:02:10,240
You and I met after
I started keeping my distance from him.

41
00:02:10,360 --> 00:02:12,600
He always looked at me
like I wanted to hit him.

42
00:02:12,680 --> 00:02:15,400
Hey, Uncle Shmuel.
-Hey, Uncle Shmuel.

43
00:02:17,440 --> 00:02:18,920
It's not you, it's not you.
He just doesn't like kids.

44
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:30,360
At first, Mom explained to me
that it’s because he doesn’t like kids,

45
00:02:31,560 --> 00:02:34,360
but later I realized it was something about me. So there’s no chance for cents,

46
00:02:34,440 --> 00:02:38,600
not for rubles and not for zlotys.
-Too bad.

47
00:02:38,760 --> 00:02:40,720
I'm going to steal some schnitzels.

48
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:42,160
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

49
00:02:42,840 --> 00:02:44,560
Hey.
-Hey, man, what's up? How's it going, babe?

50
00:02:44,760 --> 00:02:47,360
What's happening?
-All good.

51
00:02:50,200 --> 00:02:51,520
Is there some new drama in the Rosen family
I need to know about?

52
00:02:51,600 --> 00:02:54,400
Uncle Shmuel...
-Is he coming?

53
00:02:54,480 --> 00:02:56,120
No, on the contrary. He’s dead.

54
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:57,520
No way. You're kidding me?

55
00:02:57,600 --> 00:02:59,800
No, no.
-I'm dying.

56
00:02:59,880 --> 00:03:01,560
Wow, what a story. You don’t remember
what he did to me at our wedding.

57
00:03:01,720 --> 00:03:04,280
No, I wasn’t there, I was
postpartum but I heard the story.

58
00:03:04,360 --> 00:03:06,560
Well, what you didn’t hear is that... okay, listen.

59
00:03:06,680 --> 00:03:09,360
Remember I had that dress,

60
00:03:09,560 --> 00:03:10,520
נכון הייתה לי את השמלה הזאת,

61
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:12,000
The amazing one with the...
-Yeah, yeah.

62
00:03:12,080 --> 00:03:14,080
I saw her in the photo album.
-No, but you can't see it in the pictures either...

63
00:03:14,160 --> 00:03:17,160
No, I also saw the video tape.
-No, no, you can't see it in the video either...

64
00:03:17,240 --> 00:03:20,280
I also saw the slideshow you posted
on Facebook. It was just hilarious.

65
00:03:20,360 --> 00:03:21,320
What was hilarious?

66
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:22,760
Hilarious.
-Right? It turned out stunning!

67
00:03:22,840 --> 00:03:25,160
No, but you can't see
how Uncle Shmuel was trying to peek at my cleavage the whole wedding.

68
00:03:25,640 --> 00:03:27,000
Now, from the moment you caught him, that little dwarf,

69
00:03:29,840 --> 00:03:31,880
he was so stressed he just spilled a glass of wine on me.

70
00:03:31,960 --> 00:03:34,000
Do you know how hot I got? I yelled at him,

71
00:03:37,080 --> 00:03:39,240
I dried him out there in front of everyone.
I thought he was going to die right there.

72
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:43,360
In short, in my modesty! I'm definitely not in the clear.
-Hold on a second.

73
00:03:44,480 --> 00:03:47,680
Hey.
-Hey, Michal. Where's Tamari? I was already worried.

74
00:03:51,120 --> 00:03:54,960
Itamar is looking for parking, he's on his way up,
and... Riki, may you know no more sorrow.

75
00:03:55,040 --> 00:03:58,280
Oh, yeah. Sure.
-Riki

76
00:03:59,280 --> 00:04:02,200
Gershon, they left the flowers
at your place again. I really can't believe it.

77
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:08,360
I told them clearly not to send
flowers while I'm napping in the afternoon.

78
00:04:08,680 --> 00:04:13,480
But go talk to the wall.
-Who sent them?

79
00:04:13,760 --> 00:04:16,079
Me. If I don't send myself flowers, who will send me?

80
00:04:16,160 --> 00:04:19,880
These are a bit too colorful.
I wanted something a bit sadder.

81
00:04:19,959 --> 00:04:24,080
Sit down, my sweet,
could you take this vase

82
00:04:24,480 --> 00:04:27,840
and fill it with water, if it's not too much trouble?
-No, no. It's no trouble at all.

83
00:04:28,240 --> 00:04:32,080
I'll take these to the kitchen.

84
00:04:32,560 --> 00:04:34,040
Hey, Gershon, what's up? What,
is this for me? You didn't have to, Gershon.

85
00:04:39,880 --> 00:04:44,440
Oh, lilies. Why, who died?
-Uncle Shmuel.

86
00:04:44,920 --> 00:04:47,320
Enough. How much did she get?
-We don't know yet. Waiting for Miami.

87
00:04:47,480 --> 00:04:50,560
Enough. What a drama.
-No, I'm dying.

88
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:53,040
Wow!

89
00:04:58,240 --> 00:04:59,080
Oh! I got scared. Pinchas, Pinchas, I'm so...

90
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:02,360
I'm sorry, I didn't know you were there.

91
00:05:02,560 --> 00:05:03,800
Pinchas, I'm so sorry.
-It's okay. Sit down, nothing happened.

92
00:05:03,880 --> 00:05:06,560
Wow, I'm dying. Pinchas, put something on.

93
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:10,960
No, I'm dying.
-Did you hear about Uncle Shmuel?

94
00:05:11,080 --> 00:05:12,680
He drained the juice until he left.

95
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:14,000
We heard.
-All good.

96
00:05:14,080 --> 00:05:14,920
Get dressed, we're going out. Okay?

97
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:17,520
Sorry, in the...
-Sorry, in the...

98
00:05:17,600 --> 00:05:20,000
Who yelled?
-No, it's okay, it's okay.

99
00:05:21,520 --> 00:05:23,600
Shabbat Shalom, Mom.

100
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:24,920
Wait, are you guys okay?
-Physically yes, mentally a bit less.

101
00:05:25,280 --> 00:05:28,400
Riki, I'm so sorry. I went into the shower,

102
00:05:28,480 --> 00:05:31,160
I didn't know Pinchas was in there.
-No, I'm dying.

103
00:05:31,320 --> 00:05:33,640
You don't die that quickly.
I was also scared when I saw Pinchas

104
00:05:34,120 --> 00:05:37,400
for the first time in the shower.
A week later, I married him.

105
00:05:37,520 --> 00:05:41,520
Yeah, just that, from the shock, my vase fell.

106
00:05:41,600 --> 00:05:44,360
Did it break?
-Yeah. I'm so sorry, Riki.

107
00:05:44,920 --> 00:05:48,320
There's a lot of glass there but I'll cry
about it, I just need to wait for...

108
00:05:48,400 --> 00:05:51,880
Pinchas to get dressed.
-Nothing happened. It's just a vase.

109
00:05:52,320 --> 00:05:55,680
The main thing is that everyone is healthy.

110
00:05:56,120 --> 00:05:57,760
What an embarrassment, God.
-What a relief it wasn't me who broke it.

111
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:04,080
How weird that it happened
on the day Uncle Shmuel died.

112
00:06:04,440 --> 00:06:07,120
I couldn't stand that Uncle Shmuel.

113
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:08,840
Why?
-You know the first time

114
00:06:08,920 --> 00:06:10,280
I saw him was
when Shai and I started dating.

115
00:06:10,360 --> 00:06:12,880
It was the first time I sat here.

116
00:06:13,160 --> 00:06:14,720
Early in the morning, I went into the shower before everyone woke up.

117
00:06:15,280 --> 00:06:17,840
My mom hears a girl from a mile away.

118
00:06:18,680 --> 00:06:20,440
What we didn't know, Shai and I, was that
Uncle Shmuel was also visiting here.

119
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:24,440
Hello.

120
00:06:32,280 --> 00:06:33,120
שלום.

121
00:06:36,920 --> 00:06:37,840
Hi.

122
00:06:39,240 --> 00:06:42,760
No, I would’ve died.
-And since then, every time we saw him,

123
00:06:42,840 --> 00:06:45,680
he would wink at me. And the craziest part is
Shai didn’t believe me,

124
00:06:45,760 --> 00:06:48,440
he thought I was imagining it.
-No, I would’ve died. Died.

125
00:06:48,760 --> 00:06:51,600
You said he was a problematic guy.
I’m taking this course now,

126
00:06:51,680 --> 00:06:54,280
Introduction to Psychology. He fits
the definition of a problematic person,

127
00:06:54,440 --> 00:06:57,080
by definition.
-Can someone take these flowers from me?

128
00:06:57,200 --> 00:06:59,560
Because I’m starting to feel like
a beauty queen and I’m not into it.

129
00:06:59,640 --> 00:07:01,640
Tell me, what’s going on there?
-Dad got glass in his foot.

130
00:07:01,720 --> 00:07:05,320
Where?
-What do you mean where? In his foot.

131
00:07:05,880 --> 00:07:08,080
And where’s Shai?
-Taking care of the injured.

132
00:07:09,160 --> 00:07:11,680
Ouch, ouch, ow, ow.
-Why are you yelling? I haven’t touched it yet.

133
00:07:11,880 --> 00:07:13,600
Why are you yelling? He hasn’t touched it yet.

134
00:07:13,760 --> 00:07:16,240
What do you see, Shai? Is it serious?
Needs stitches, right?

135
00:07:16,440 --> 00:07:18,560
No, not at all. It’s just a small piece of glass.
-Oh.

136
00:07:18,720 --> 00:07:20,560
Ouch, ouch, ow, ow.
-Stop yelling.

137
00:07:20,640 --> 00:07:23,240
The neighbors will think we’re killing someone.

138
00:07:23,320 --> 00:07:25,120
Ouch, ouch.
-That’s it. I got it out.

139
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:29,160
You got it all out? Do me a favor,
check again to make sure you got it all.

140
00:07:29,240 --> 00:07:30,120
For sure.
-Definitely.

141
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:32,920
Yeah. Just a small piece of glass.
-See? You’re still alive.

142
00:07:34,160 --> 00:07:36,280
I’m going to flip the schnitzels,
so they don’t burn.

143
00:07:37,040 --> 00:07:40,320
Schnitzels? That’s what’s important to you?
I almost lost my leg,

144
00:07:40,440 --> 00:07:44,320
and she’s only thinking about schnitzels.
-There, done. I put on a band-aid.

145
00:07:44,400 --> 00:07:47,480
Thanks, Shai. By the way, have you heard about Uncle Shmuel?

146
00:07:47,560 --> 00:07:51,280
Yeah. It was about time, right?
-Yeah, but still, it’s sad.

147
00:07:51,560 --> 00:07:54,080
Just so you know, he was the only one
from Mom’s side that I really liked.

148
00:07:54,160 --> 00:07:56,120
We had amazing conversations.
-What?

149
00:07:56,200 --> 00:07:58,040
Of course, very deep conversations.

150
00:07:58,880 --> 00:08:02,080
Ariel Sharon scares them.
They say he came in with bandanas

151
00:08:02,240 --> 00:08:04,760
to the Knesset. He talks in a funny way.

152
00:08:04,840 --> 00:08:08,720
Here, here, here, here... I can’t do impressions,

153
00:08:08,960 --> 00:08:10,840
but I do animals really well.

154
00:08:12,880 --> 00:08:15,360
This one is very economical. Do you see the engine?

155
00:08:15,920 --> 00:08:20,160
But this one, it’s really good for long
trips. Not that I travel far,

156
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:23,400
but, you know, sometimes I want
to get to "Asaf Harofeh" hospital

157
00:08:23,560 --> 00:08:25,080
or "Yarkon" cemetery...

158
00:08:28,360 --> 00:08:31,560
I tell him, listen, I’m the angel of death.
How come you’re not afraid of me?

159
00:08:31,880 --> 00:08:33,960
And he says, why should I be scared of the angel of death

160
00:08:34,280 --> 00:08:36,559
if I’ve been married to his sister for 35 years?

161
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:46,880
Uncle Shmuel had a great sense of humor.
-What are you saying? Are you serious?

162
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:50,240
I don’t think I ever heard him
say a word besides yelling.

163
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:53,160
He didn’t like kids.
-Even when I grew up.

164
00:08:53,240 --> 00:08:55,560
That was just a phrase Mom would
say to calm me down.

165
00:08:55,640 --> 00:08:57,640
It was Mom who forced him to talk to us.

166
00:08:57,800 --> 00:09:00,760
He wasn’t a big talker, but he knew how to listen.

167
00:09:00,840 --> 00:09:03,200
How old was he, actually? Because even
when we were kids, he was old.

168
00:09:03,280 --> 00:09:06,040
Even when I met him 50 years ago, he was old.

169
00:09:06,120 --> 00:09:09,400
Everyone thought he was going to die
any minute. He was loaded with money,

170
00:09:09,480 --> 00:09:12,360
and that’s why your mom’s whole family
was kissing up to him.

171
00:09:12,440 --> 00:09:13,360
Forgive me for the expression.

172
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:15,360
It sounds better in Yiddish.
-I doubt it.

173
00:09:15,440 --> 00:09:18,880
Why? Kisch zayne tokhes
-Please.

174
00:09:21,920 --> 00:09:24,240
I cleaned the glasses, Riki.
-And I washed.

175
00:09:24,560 --> 00:09:26,680
Really?
-No. I was keeping an eye on Shabi.

176
00:09:26,760 --> 00:09:29,960
Nonsense. I’ll go over it
later anyway. You shouldn’t have.

177
00:09:30,440 --> 00:09:32,480
I’m really sorry, Riki, I really am. I...

178
00:09:32,800 --> 00:09:35,680
Just tell me where I can buy one
and I’ll get you a new one.

179
00:09:35,760 --> 00:09:39,280
Forget it, Shabi, it’s not necessary,
and besides, there’s nowhere to buy one like that.

180
00:09:39,360 --> 00:09:41,360
What? I’m sure I can get you one like that and a vase.

181
00:09:41,440 --> 00:09:43,720
She got her degree in shopping, Mom.

182
00:09:43,800 --> 00:09:48,600
This is the vase I got as a gift from Uncle Shmuel.
That's why I wanted to use it.

183
00:09:49,080 --> 00:09:53,480
Besides, it's an antique vase.
-Ugly. You’ve been hiding it since Shavuot.

184
00:09:54,040 --> 00:09:57,640
Itamar, if you don’t have
anything smart to say, it’s better to stay quiet.

185
00:09:57,880 --> 00:10:00,640
Wow, Riki, I’m so sorry.
I really feel bad about this.

186
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:04,160
Forget it, sit down, it’s nothing. Just a vase.

187
00:10:04,280 --> 00:10:06,800
Anyway, I wasn’t planning to take it with me to the grave.

188
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:13,320
The main thing is everyone is healthy. Everything else is nonsense.
-Riki, I really...

189
00:10:13,800 --> 00:10:15,760
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

190
00:10:15,840 --> 00:10:18,360
Hey Adam, what’s up? What’s this, alone?

191
00:10:18,880 --> 00:10:19,840
Bar Refaeli is parking the antenna.

192
00:10:20,400 --> 00:10:21,640
Really?
-Yeah.

193
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:27,000
No. So what’s going on? Have they called
from Miami yet? Did we get anything?

194
00:10:27,560 --> 00:10:31,160
How did you hear the dwarf kicked the bucket?
-What happened to you? Mom called me right away.

195
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:35,400
Nothing. Every time something happens.
War, revolution in Egypt,

196
00:10:35,520 --> 00:10:39,000
plane crash, tsunami in Japan, dog in a dress,

197
00:10:39,120 --> 00:10:42,040
Mom calls right away to check if I’m okay.
-Wow.

198
00:10:42,160 --> 00:10:44,920
She never calls me.
I always have to call her.

199
00:10:45,080 --> 00:10:48,080
They haven’t called yet.
-So what? It’s nice here.

200
00:10:48,160 --> 00:10:49,360
Not more than usual.

201
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:54,240
Tell me, do you think there’s any chance
you’ll get a piece of the inheritance?

202
00:10:54,800 --> 00:10:58,840
Where? Uncle Shmuel hasn’t liked me
since that thing at the wedding

203
00:10:58,960 --> 00:11:00,920
of mine and Michal’s.
-Why? What happened?

204
00:11:01,560 --> 00:11:04,880
I was at the wedding, I was dead drunk.

205
00:11:05,720 --> 00:11:09,320
It was a great wedding. People came in droves.

206
00:11:09,400 --> 00:11:12,600
But at some point, when I was standing
next to the... what’s her name,

207
00:11:12,840 --> 00:11:14,600
the second cousin, the one with the lazy eye...

208
00:11:14,760 --> 00:11:18,960
Never mind, anyway, I lost
my balance and crashed there.

209
00:11:20,880 --> 00:11:22,320
Pervert! You pervert!

210
00:11:22,400 --> 00:11:24,760
He noticed I was pointing at him and before
he could say anything to me,

211
00:11:24,960 --> 00:11:28,400
Michal opened her mouth at him...
all the nerves she had

212
00:11:28,520 --> 00:11:30,800
about the catering she took out on him.
-Yeah, the food was terrible.

213
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:34,880
Yeah, but the alcohol was top-notch. In short, there’s
no way I’m seeing anything from his inheritance.

214
00:11:35,360 --> 00:11:37,720
Hey, aren’t you ashamed?
-About what?

215
00:11:37,800 --> 00:11:40,120
Couldn’t you have told me you did
that? You know what a scene

216
00:11:40,240 --> 00:11:42,440
I made about him? You know
what I said to him?

217
00:11:42,560 --> 00:11:46,240
Wow, poor guy. I’m dying. What an embarrassment.
I called him a "smelly dwarf."

218
00:11:46,320 --> 00:11:48,360
But, Mom, he really was smelly.
-I think I’m going to fall!

219
00:11:48,440 --> 00:11:51,600
I kicked him in the leg at some point.
I hope it was the leg.

220
00:11:51,960 --> 00:11:54,440
No, I’m dying. What an embarrassment.
Don’t talk to me anymore.

221
00:11:54,560 --> 00:11:56,800
Mom, come on, I was drunk.

222
00:11:57,320 --> 00:12:01,200
Out of joy, Mom, out of joy. Mom! Mom!

223
00:12:01,280 --> 00:12:06,120
And he got the vase from his mom, my grandma,

224
00:12:06,680 --> 00:12:09,440
and she got it as a gift from her mom.

225
00:12:09,520 --> 00:12:14,440
Wow! That was a really old vase.
-Yeah. Very.

226
00:12:14,520 --> 00:12:17,040
That’s why I was so excited when he gave it to me.

227
00:12:17,120 --> 00:12:20,680
You know that this vase
was with them throughout the Holocaust?

228
00:12:21,440 --> 00:12:23,680
I don’t understand how he managed to do that.

229
00:12:23,760 --> 00:12:28,840
And it’s not like I haven’t heard stories
about a ring, at most a watch,

230
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:32,600
but a vase? And he was such a cheapskate, Uncle Shmuel.

231
00:12:32,760 --> 00:12:35,080
How he managed to hide it, I don’t know.

232
00:12:35,560 --> 00:12:38,120
That’s why I was so excited when he gave it to me.

233
00:12:38,200 --> 00:12:42,840
So it had sentimental value too.
-You bet.

234
00:12:51,240 --> 00:12:53,760
At first, I didn’t know how to appreciate it,

235
00:13:01,920 --> 00:13:04,840
and Uncle Shmuel, who was a sensitive man,

236
00:13:04,960 --> 00:13:06,800
got a bit offended, I think.

237
00:13:12,600 --> 00:13:13,920
Uncle Shmuel, look. I cleaned.

238
00:13:20,880 --> 00:13:22,320
Uncle Shmuel.

239
00:13:22,640 --> 00:13:25,960
Just a few weeks later, I found out how much it’s worth.

240
00:13:26,120 --> 00:13:28,080
Was it expensive?
-Very.

241
00:13:28,160 --> 00:13:33,040
I have a friend who studied appraisals and treasures
and he checked the vase.

242
00:13:33,200 --> 00:13:37,360
He said not only was it expensive,
it was also very, very rare.

243
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:41,000
It was made in the East using a very ancient technique,

244
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:45,360
and the workers who made it used lead paint.

245
00:13:45,920 --> 00:13:50,280
Most of the workers who produced
these vases died,

246
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:54,240
which is why they stopped making it.
-Lead...

247
00:13:54,720 --> 00:13:57,400
That's why it was so rare.

248
00:13:57,760 --> 00:14:03,080
When I insured the house, I insured
that vase for 2,500 shekels.

249
00:14:03,160 --> 00:14:06,280
That's how the insurance expert valued it.
-How nice!

250
00:14:06,440 --> 00:14:08,840
So you’re calming me down a bit.
That means the vase is insured.

251
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:12,160
You’ll get your money back.
-You’re so sweet sometimes.

252
00:14:12,560 --> 00:14:17,720
The vase was insured against theft.
Human error isn’t covered.

253
00:14:18,560 --> 00:14:22,360
Where's Pinchas? We need to do the Kiddush.

254
00:14:24,040 --> 00:14:27,840
Wow, lucky it wasn’t me who broke it.

255
00:14:31,120 --> 00:14:32,840
Get your hand off me.

256
00:14:32,920 --> 00:14:34,400
Come on, Dad, you’ll be fine.

257
00:14:36,800 --> 00:14:39,360
Pinchas, what are you doing here?
-Oh, my goodness.

258
00:14:39,440 --> 00:14:42,680
Get up, you need to do the Kiddush.
-Rivka, I’m not feeling well.

259
00:14:42,760 --> 00:14:45,440
What, because of the glass in your foot?
-It hurts.

260
00:14:45,520 --> 00:14:49,640
Oh come on, it’s just a little cut with a band-aid.
What, are you a little kid? Come on, get up already.

261
00:14:49,720 --> 00:14:53,200
Rivka, it hurts. Maybe there's still a shard in my foot.

262
00:14:53,320 --> 00:14:56,760
I can feel it moving
in my veins. It’s heading to my head, Rivka.

263
00:14:56,840 --> 00:15:00,320
Oh, what are you talking about? It’s just a scratch.

264
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:03,360
Stop being such a baby and come help me a bit.

265
00:15:03,520 --> 00:15:06,320
Don’t you understand that it hurts?
I’m telling you, it hurts.

266
00:15:06,400 --> 00:15:08,320
I don’t know why. Maybe the wound got infected.

267
00:15:08,520 --> 00:15:11,040
I feel like the infection has spread to my other foot too.

268
00:15:11,120 --> 00:15:14,000
How could it have gotten infected already? It just happened three minutes ago,

269
00:15:14,080 --> 00:15:18,000
and besides, Mr. Rosen, my floor is clean.

270
00:15:18,160 --> 00:15:22,440
Yours is cleaner than an operating room, come on.
-There have been cases where they had to amputate.

271
00:15:22,600 --> 00:15:25,520
What will I do without a leg?
Rivka, promise me you won’t let them

272
00:15:25,600 --> 00:15:27,800
take my leg. Promise.
-Oh, dear.

273
00:15:27,920 --> 00:15:30,920
If it comes to that, remember,
you promised. You’re my promise.

274
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:34,760
No, no, no. I don’t mind dying.
I’ve seen and done everything.

275
00:15:34,840 --> 00:15:38,480
Okay, fine. I promise.
They won’t take your leg. Okay?

276
00:15:38,600 --> 00:15:39,680
Thanks.
-Come on, get up already.

277
00:15:40,320 --> 00:15:44,720
And Rivka, after I die, you can
go out with Giora. I give you my blessing.

278
00:15:45,400 --> 00:15:49,000
Which Giora?
-Giora, Giora. The one you used to hang out with.

279
00:15:49,520 --> 00:15:53,560
The one you met at the disco, "Calypso."
-Giora Habakin?

280
00:15:53,640 --> 00:15:56,040
Giora Habakin.
-He passed away ten weeks ago.

281
00:15:56,120 --> 00:16:00,120
See? First Giora, then
David Shmuel, and now it’s my turn.

282
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:04,320
Okay, fine. Your turn has come.
But if you don’t mind first

283
00:16:04,440 --> 00:16:08,840
coming to do the Kiddush... after that
you can die as much as you want.

284
00:16:08,920 --> 00:16:13,880
And when you get up there, you can go out
with Giora. I approve.

285
00:16:13,960 --> 00:16:17,600
I’m sure you haven’t done that yet. Get up already!

286
00:16:20,240 --> 00:16:22,360
Are we eating today too?
-I’m starving!

287
00:16:22,440 --> 00:16:26,080
Was there a phone call? Did I hear a phone?
-No, it was probably from the TV.

288
00:16:26,160 --> 00:16:28,960
So answer it, I don’t want to miss that call.

289
00:16:29,040 --> 00:16:35,080
Besides, there was a death in the family.
A little respect for the deceased. What will the neighbors say?

290
00:16:35,200 --> 00:16:38,400
Mom, it’s fine. We’re all
on phone standby. We’re on a mission.

291
00:16:38,880 --> 00:16:42,160
Okay, Shai, go get your dying dad
from the room. I want us to start.

292
00:16:42,320 --> 00:16:44,160
The food is getting cold.
-Okay.

293
00:16:45,320 --> 00:16:49,000
So, Adam, what are your chances
with David Shmuel’s will?

294
00:16:50,440 --> 00:16:53,600
I think they’re around zero.
-Why? What did you do to David Shmuel?

295
00:16:53,680 --> 00:16:55,240
Did you call me?
-No.

296
00:16:55,320 --> 00:16:56,160
Did you call me

297
00:16:56,240 --> 00:16:58,800
because there’s no way I’m going back
to the kitchen for vase stories anymore.

298
00:16:58,880 --> 00:17:02,680
Okay, sit down. Adam is just telling us
what he did to David Shmuel.

299
00:17:04,640 --> 00:17:08,240
So... I don’t know if you remember

300
00:17:08,359 --> 00:17:12,880
but at your wedding, I was pretty drunk.

301
00:17:14,920 --> 00:17:15,920
Total loss.

302
00:17:17,079 --> 00:17:21,079
So I went to the bathroom because I had to relieve myself.

303
00:17:21,160 --> 00:17:22,480
I drank a lot.

304
00:17:33,040 --> 00:17:36,480
I didn't see he was there and... I had to.

305
00:17:37,040 --> 00:17:38,920
No, I'm dying. I told you
he didn't smell good.

306
00:17:39,160 --> 00:17:42,640
I told you he stank.
-Uncle Shmuel was around a lot at the wedding, right?

307
00:17:43,120 --> 00:17:45,720
You're not normal.
-I was drunk.

308
00:17:46,360 --> 00:17:48,080
Come on, Dad. Come sit here.
-Shabbat Shalom.

309
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:49,040
Hey, Pinchas.
-Hey, Dad.

310
00:17:49,120 --> 00:17:50,080
Shabbat Shalom.

311
00:17:50,320 --> 00:17:52,160
What's up? What are you talking about?

312
00:17:52,320 --> 00:17:55,560
We're assessing who has a chance
to see something from Uncle Shmuel.

313
00:17:55,680 --> 00:17:57,720
For now, the situation doesn't look good.

314
00:17:57,800 --> 00:18:01,760
But, Dad, Uncle Shmuel
kind of liked you, right? So there's a chance...

315
00:18:01,840 --> 00:18:03,560
No chance.
-Why?

316
00:18:03,960 --> 00:18:07,160
I said I liked Uncle Shmuel.
I didn't say he liked me.

317
00:18:07,240 --> 00:18:12,680
What did you do, Dad?
-Well, at Tamari and Michal's wedding...

318
00:18:12,880 --> 00:18:15,560
I was drunk.
-No, I'm dying.

319
00:18:16,600 --> 00:18:20,720
The alcohol was flowing at the wedding and everyone had a great time.

320
00:18:21,200 --> 00:18:25,680
When I'm tipsy, I love to talk
I felt like hugging the little beggar.

321
00:18:29,160 --> 00:18:31,840
Pervert! Oh, you stupid pervert!

322
00:18:31,920 --> 00:18:33,600
Sorry to pull you away
from the family's story time

323
00:18:33,680 --> 00:18:35,680
but there's a problem.
-What happened? Talk to me.

324
00:18:35,760 --> 00:18:40,280
Turns out I broke your mom's
lead vase in the apartment and it's toxic.

325
00:18:40,400 --> 00:18:43,560
And it turns out that vase is worth 2,500 shekels.
-What? Are you sure?

326
00:18:43,640 --> 00:18:45,720
What?
-I thought that vase was worth nothing.

327
00:18:45,840 --> 00:18:48,080
Tell that to Uncle Shmuel.
That's what your mom says it's worth.

328
00:18:48,240 --> 00:18:50,120
And I have to pay you back
because otherwise I won't be able to

329
00:18:50,240 --> 00:18:52,640
look her in the eyes for the rest of my life.
-What's true is true.

330
00:18:52,720 --> 00:18:56,000
And where are we going to get 2,500 shekels now?
-Oh, where have you been?

331
00:18:56,160 --> 00:19:00,040
I was already worried. Come on,
we're starting. Everyone's already seated.

332
00:19:00,120 --> 00:19:02,560
Ben, come on, come on. I'm not feeling well.

333
00:19:02,640 --> 00:19:04,200
Let's wrap this up, Ben.

334
00:19:07,960 --> 00:19:09,440
"On the sixth day, the heavens were finished..."

335
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:12,560
Did you bring wine?
-Where? I was stuck in the office all day.

336
00:19:12,640 --> 00:19:15,280
When could I move?
-What a bummer with you.

337
00:19:15,960 --> 00:19:17,360
Well, let's drink "and hammers."

338
00:19:17,520 --> 00:19:18,760
I'm starting to feel like your family has a serious

339
00:19:18,840 --> 00:19:20,040
problem.
-Quiet.

340
00:19:21,120 --> 00:19:23,880
No talking during Kiddush. A little respect.
-Sorry.

341
00:19:24,040 --> 00:19:25,720
"Sabri Maranan."
-Cheers!

342
00:19:26,120 --> 00:19:27,720
Shh.
-Sorry, come on. I can't shake this off.

343
00:19:28,720 --> 00:19:31,600
The phone. It's the phone. Pinchas.

344
00:19:33,440 --> 00:19:35,760
Pinchas.
-Come on, answer it.

345
00:19:37,720 --> 00:19:40,680
Rosen family, hello. Regina!

346
00:19:41,640 --> 00:19:44,680
Yes, Regina, open it now. Yes.

347
00:19:45,560 --> 00:19:46,600
What?

348
00:19:48,920 --> 00:19:50,000
What do you mean nothing?

349
00:19:51,440 --> 00:19:53,560
He left everything to widows and orphans?

350
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:58,600
But I'm an orphan too. Why did he write that?

351
00:19:59,360 --> 00:20:00,760
Come on, why? Why?

352
00:20:00,840 --> 00:20:03,560
He didn't like the way I treated his vase.

353
00:20:04,680 --> 00:20:08,040
Now I don't even have the pleasure
of breaking it.

354
00:20:08,160 --> 00:20:11,120
Yes, Regina. Who is this?

355
00:20:12,440 --> 00:20:15,440
Who is Shabi Hasson?
-It's me. I'm Shabi Hasson.

356
00:20:15,520 --> 00:20:18,200
No, I thought Shabi Rosen.
-No, no, but I was Hasson.

357
00:20:18,280 --> 00:20:22,240
No, but she's in the middle of Kiddush.
Okay, fine Regina. Hold on.

358
00:20:27,720 --> 00:20:30,480
Hello. Yes, this is Shabi Rosen.

359
00:20:31,480 --> 00:20:34,520
Yes, no, but when Uncle Shmuel
met me I was Shabi Hasson.

360
00:20:34,960 --> 00:20:36,360
Yes. How much?

361
00:20:37,640 --> 00:20:40,440
Seriously? Are you sure?

362
00:20:42,040 --> 00:20:45,000
Okay. Thanks. Yeah, I’ll return it.

363
00:20:45,080 --> 00:20:47,160
How much?
-2,500 shekels.

364
00:20:47,720 --> 00:20:48,920
Regina!

365
00:20:49,960 --> 00:20:52,440
What are you... uh.

366
00:20:53,080 --> 00:20:55,640
Ben! Ben!
-What was that?

367
00:20:56,040 --> 00:21:00,440
He didn’t leave anything for anyone
except 2,500 shekels for Shani Hasson.

368
00:21:00,520 --> 00:21:03,120
What? Why?
-He said a few weeks ago

369
00:21:03,200 --> 00:21:04,760
she brought him a lot of joy.

370
00:21:08,160 --> 00:21:11,480
No, I’m dying.
-Rebecca, I’m not feeling well.

371
00:21:11,800 --> 00:21:14,920
Me too, Pinchas. Me too.

372
00:21:17,160 --> 00:21:20,080
My aunt, Regina, with the walker and the oxygen tank

373
00:21:20,440 --> 00:21:22,120
would have passed you.
-Funny.

374
00:21:23,080 --> 00:21:25,720
Do you think he’ll be okay?
-They said in the ER he’ll be fine.

375
00:21:26,120 --> 00:21:29,120
He didn’t absorb much lead. Not fatal
but he’ll need to stay for observation.

376
00:21:29,800 --> 00:21:30,880
Poor Pinchas.

377
00:21:30,960 --> 00:21:33,680
My mom, on the other hand, I’m not sure she’ll recover
from not getting anything.

378
00:21:33,800 --> 00:21:36,360
Yeah, at least you paid her for that poison vase,

379
00:21:36,440 --> 00:21:38,720
so she won’t torture me for life
about breaking it.

380
00:21:38,800 --> 00:21:40,360
I’m not sure she’ll recover from that either.

381
00:21:40,520 --> 00:21:43,200
Yeah, the truth is you’re right. That’s your mom. She
will
always find something to complain about.

382
00:21:43,280 --> 00:21:44,440
It’s in her genes.

383
00:21:45,560 --> 00:21:50,120
The kids fell asleep.
-Did I tell you you’re as beautiful as the day I met you?

384
00:21:50,560 --> 00:21:53,920
Shai. You know what I just thought?
-What?

385
00:21:54,320 --> 00:22:00,520
If a peek at what I have to offer cost Uncle Shmuel
2,500 shekels, how much do you owe me?

386
00:22:00,800 --> 00:22:04,000
I think I need
a few more peeks before I decide.

387
00:22:04,800 --> 00:22:07,520
Do you have cash for tonight?
-Do you take credit?

388
00:22:09,800 --> 00:22:12,360
Dov... Shai... you said Dvir.

389
00:22:13,200 --> 00:22:15,920
What are you seeing, Dvir? Why are you saying "Dvir"?

390
00:22:16,280 --> 00:22:17,560
This thing stuck to me.

391
00:22:28,040 --> 00:22:30,080
You didn’t press well.
-My mom did something to the light.

392
00:22:30,640 --> 00:22:32,280
A piece of glass got into Dad’s foot.

393
00:22:32,360 --> 00:22:33,840
Where?
-Sorry. Sorry.

394
00:22:36,040 --> 00:22:38,360
Have they called from Miami yet? Did we get anything?

395
00:22:38,480 --> 00:22:40,720
No, no, no, this is the only place

396
00:22:40,800 --> 00:22:42,400
Call! Have they called from Miami yet?

397
00:22:42,480 --> 00:22:43,760
I told you no.
-Oh, shoot.

398
00:22:45,840 --> 00:22:47,280
What a pavlova.

399
00:22:47,360 --> 00:22:48,960
I’m sorry I pulled you out in the middle of story time

400
00:22:49,040 --> 00:22:51,520
with your alcoholic family.
-Sorry.

401
00:22:51,600 --> 00:22:52,760
Why are you laughing?

402
00:22:53,440 --> 00:22:54,280
Phone.

403
00:22:54,640 --> 00:22:55,960
Joy! Uh...

